
Using SQL directly or from R/Python.

Start with an existing database.

Database
  Collection of tables.
  As with CSV/Dataframes, etc.
    Tables have rows and columns
      Columns are variables
      Rows correspond to observations

    All observations can be in a single table
    But databases encourage avoiding redundancy

    Consider repeated observations -

a person attending a doctor
    First Name, Last Name, Date of Birth, Date, Blood pressure, Temperature, Weight, Height, ..
    Duncan, Temple Lang, 12/3/1968,1/1/17,160,98.6,180,73
    Duncan, Temple Lang, 12/3/1968,6/1/17,170,96.8,185,73.5

Climate information
  Station,Address,Longitude,Latitude,Precipitation,Humidity,Temperature
  S123,



